What's the way here? A:

Something that I have used in the past is Mongo Jack. This provides a simple wrapper that, according to their documentation, directly maps POJOs from the Mongo stream, without the intermediary SimpleDBObject. This also uses the Jackson library, so you can use Jackson serialization and de-serialization annotations. This is what the website says:

Deserialises queried objects directly from the MongoDB stream, making it one of the (if not the) fastest object mappers for MongoDB out there. Perhaps this is what you are looking for, yes? Here's the example from the website:
JacksonDBCollection<MyObject, String> coll = JacksonDBCollection.wrap(dbCollection, MyObject.class,
 String.class);
MyObject myObject = ...
WriteResult<MyObject, String> result = coll.insert(myObject);
String id = result.getSavedId();
MyObject savedObject = coll.findOneById(id);

