Q:

How to return an array in UPPAAL? I am trying to return an integer array in an UPPAAL function. What is the correct syntax for that? This code snippet doesn't work:
int[] randomTest(int N)
{
 int test[2];
 test[0] = 0;
 test[1] = 1;
 return test;
}

A:

Arrays are allowed for clocks, channels, constants and integer variables. They are defined by appending a size to the variable name, 
e.g. chan c[4]; clock a[2]; int[3,5] u[7];. Initialisers are used to initialise integer variables and arrays of integer variables.

